{"data":{"post":{"id":"fb1df905-73f9-579b-9aae-4b6899d089dd","html":"<p>Have you been bother about the complex UI in Word when you just want to write some notes? Have you wondered whether there is a way to simply type maths expression? If you have the same complain as me, markdown would be the best solution.</p>\n<h4>Reasons for using Markdown</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>easy to use</li>\n<li>easy to integrate with Latex and other utilities</li>\n<li>easy to export into other format (e.g. pdf, html, docx, rtf)</li>\n<li>lightweight</li>\n<li>code highlighting</li>\n<li>universal access (most editors are cross-platform)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>(some features are not supported by all editors)</p>\n<h3>🌈 Get start with markdown</h3>\n<p>First of all, you need an editor to start with. Personally, I recommand to use <a href=\"https://www.typora.io/\">Typora</a>. Just click the link or go to <a href=\"https://www.typora.io/\">https://www.typora.io/</a>. Scroll to bottom and there choose the version for your OS. In this article, I will use MasOS version to demonstrate.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/downloadTypora-139bc018d2df741b24118e00e86734d8-36f7d.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 57.99648506151143%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"download Typora\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/downloadTypora-139bc018d2df741b24118e00e86734d8-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/downloadTypora-139bc018d2df741b24118e00e86734d8-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/downloadTypora-139bc018d2df741b24118e00e86734d8-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/downloadTypora-139bc018d2df741b24118e00e86734d8-48538.png 800w,\n/static/downloadTypora-139bc018d2df741b24118e00e86734d8-36f7d.png 1138w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The start screen of Typora is minimalism with only the essential info.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/typoraStartScreen-5d55e2834d3a5739fd9e65c15ea78d2b-b76a6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 74.83059051306873%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"typora start screen\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/typoraStartScreen-5d55e2834d3a5739fd9e65c15ea78d2b-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/typoraStartScreen-5d55e2834d3a5739fd9e65c15ea78d2b-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/typoraStartScreen-5d55e2834d3a5739fd9e65c15ea78d2b-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/typoraStartScreen-5d55e2834d3a5739fd9e65c15ea78d2b-48538.png 800w,\n/static/typoraStartScreen-5d55e2834d3a5739fd9e65c15ea78d2b-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/typoraStartScreen-5d55e2834d3a5739fd9e65c15ea78d2b-d134a.png 1600w,\n/static/typoraStartScreen-5d55e2834d3a5739fd9e65c15ea78d2b-b76a6.png 2066w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>You can quick edit the file location and name by clicking the file name, and see stats on the right top of the window. More settings can be found in the menu bar.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/TyporaSettings-3be1be49096667607a825b7f23f8d32b-b76a6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 74.83059051306873%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"Typora settings\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/TyporaSettings-3be1be49096667607a825b7f23f8d32b-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/TyporaSettings-3be1be49096667607a825b7f23f8d32b-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/TyporaSettings-3be1be49096667607a825b7f23f8d32b-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/TyporaSettings-3be1be49096667607a825b7f23f8d32b-48538.png 800w,\n/static/TyporaSettings-3be1be49096667607a825b7f23f8d32b-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/TyporaSettings-3be1be49096667607a825b7f23f8d32b-d134a.png 1600w,\n/static/TyporaSettings-3be1be49096667607a825b7f23f8d32b-b76a6.png 2066w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>OK, so now I’ve set up the editor, but what is markdown? 🤔</h3>\n<p>Wikipedia would tell you that</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Markdown</strong> is a lightweight markup language with plain text formatting syntax. Its design allows it to be converted to many output formats, but the original tool by the same name only supports HTML Markdown is often used to format readme files, for writing messages in online discussion forums, and to create rich text using a plain text editor.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Let me show you what this means.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/sourceCode-cf867a0acc0a4ec9af009d35b46dd8bc-0919d.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 71.90008920606601%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"source code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/sourceCode-cf867a0acc0a4ec9af009d35b46dd8bc-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/sourceCode-cf867a0acc0a4ec9af009d35b46dd8bc-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/sourceCode-cf867a0acc0a4ec9af009d35b46dd8bc-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/sourceCode-cf867a0acc0a4ec9af009d35b46dd8bc-48538.png 800w,\n/static/sourceCode-cf867a0acc0a4ec9af009d35b46dd8bc-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/sourceCode-cf867a0acc0a4ec9af009d35b46dd8bc-d134a.png 1600w,\n/static/sourceCode-cf867a0acc0a4ec9af009d35b46dd8bc-0919d.png 2242w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Markdown file markups text which can be recognised by editors or viewers as <strong>effects</strong>. For example, different levels of title are recognised by the number of #, one # indicates level one title. You can definitely add effects on text using code, but I prefer to use keyboard shortcuts. On macOS, <code class=\"language-text\">⌘ 1</code> change the current line into a level one title. And you can change the title level by <code class=\"language-text\">⌘ -</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">⌘ =</code>.</p>\n<h4>List of a few shortcuts for Typora on macOS</h4>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"center\">Bold</th>\n<th></th>\n<th align=\"center\">Emphasis</th>\n<th align=\"center\">Underline</th>\n<th align=\"center\">Code</th>\n<th align=\"center\">Quote</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\">⌘ B</td>\n<td></td>\n<td align=\"center\">⌘ I</td>\n<td align=\"center\">⌘ U</td>\n<td align=\"center\">⌥ ⌘ X</td>\n<td align=\"center\">⌥ ⌘ Q</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>+---+\n| a |\n+---+</p>\n<p>You can find a full list of shortcuts in the <a href=\"http://support.typora.io/Shortcut-Keys/\">here</a>.</p>\n<h3>How to embed Maths expression</h3>\n<p>Typora provides two ways for embedding maths expressions. <strong>Inline maths</strong> and <strong>maths block</strong>.</p>\n<h4>Inline maths</h4>\n<p>With inline maths, you can embed a maths expression e.g. <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">y=x^2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> in text line.</p>\n<h4>Maths block</h4>\n<p>Maths block allows you to display maths expression in individual space.</p>\n<span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></msubsup><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>f</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi>ξ</mi><mtext> </mtext><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>ξ</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mtext> </mtext><mi>d</mi><mi>ξ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f(x) = \\int_{-\\infty}^\\infty\n    \\hat f\\xi\\,e^{2 \\pi i \\xi x}\n    \\,d\\xi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.384573em;vertical-align:-0.970281em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol large-op\" style=\"margin-right:0.44445em;position:relative;top:-0.0011249999999999316em;\">∫</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.414292em;\"><span style=\"top:-1.7880500000000001em;margin-left:-0.44445em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">∞</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.8129000000000004em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">∞</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.970281em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.9578799999999998em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span><span style=\"top:-3.26344em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.08332999999999999em;\"><span class=\"mord\">^</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.19444em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.04601em;\">ξ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">e</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8991079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.1130000000000004em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.04601em;\">ξ</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">x</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">d</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.04601em;\">ξ</span></span></span></span></span>","fields":{"slug":"/Markdown/","prefix":"2019-11-15"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Markdown","author":"yujie wang","category":"“utilities\"","cover":null}},"authornote":{"id":"7dca60f9-6174-5308-b1d6-29aa40a88701","html":"<p><strong>Yujie</strong> 电子信息在读, 业余程序员, 喜欢捣腾网络开发。Amateur web developer, currently study Electronic and Information Engineering in Imperial College London.</p>"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"facebook":{"appId":"..."}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Markdown/","prev":{"id":"8dd00b24-9a41-5284-b586-87633480e117","fields":{"slug":"/Richmond-Park/","prefix":"2019-10-19","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"An Afternoon in Richmond Park","category":"london"}},"source":"posts"}}